&lt;li&gt;Ensure all employment documentation is legally compliant, up to date and aligned with US federal and state requirements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with legal counsel where required on complex or non-standard employment arrangements&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own end-to-end US benefits administration health, dental, vision, 401(k), wellness reimbursements and all ancillary benefits&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage open enrolment processes, vendor relationships and employee benefits queries with accuracy and care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure benefits programmes are competitive, compliant and clearly communicated to all US employees&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design, write and maintain US people policies that are legally compliant, clearly written and genuinely employee-friendly&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proactively track changes in AMER federal and state employment law and update policies and practices before they become a problem&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure our US Employee Handbook is current, consistent and reflects who we are as a company&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage all US immigration processes including H-1B, OPT, STEM OPT, green card sponsorship and I-9 compliance&lt;/li&gt;
